by_category.label: gftools-builder (config.yaml)
by_category.description: Repositories using gftools-builder with a config.yaml file. This is the modern, recommended approach for Google Fonts. The config.yaml specifies source files and build options, and gftools-builder orchestrates the compilation pipeline (typically using fontmake under the hood).

by_category.label: gftools-builder via Makefile
by_category.description: Repositories that invoke gftools-builder through a Makefile rather than using config.yaml directly. This was a transitional pattern before config.yaml became standard.

by_category.label: fontmake (direct)
by_category.description: Repositories that call fontmake directly (via Makefile, build.sh, or build.py) without going through gftools-builder. fontmake compiles .glyphs, .ufo, and .designspace sources into binary font files.

by_category.label: Custom Python build script
by_category.description: Repositories with a custom build.py script that uses tools other than fontmake or gftools-builder. These may use specialized pipelines or custom compilation steps.

by_category.label: Custom Shell build script
by_category.description: Repositories with a custom build.sh shell script that uses tools other than fontmake or gftools-builder. Similar to custom Python builds but implemented as shell scripts.

by_category.label: Makefile (other)
by_category.description: Repositories with a Makefile that doesn't invoke gftools-builder or fontmake. These may use other font compilation tools or have non-standard build processes.

by_category.label: Travis CI only
by_category.description: Repositories where the only build configuration is a .travis.yml file with no local build scripts. The build was handled entirely by Travis CI, which is now deprecated.

by_category.label: GitHub Actions only
by_category.description: Repositories where the only build configuration is in GitHub Actions workflow files, with no local build scripts. The build runs entirely in CI.

by_category.label: Source only (no build system)
by_category.description: Repositories that contain font source files (.glyphs, .ufo, .designspace, .sfd) but have no build system configured. These fonts were likely compiled manually or using a process not captured in the repository.

by_category.label: Pre-built binaries only
by_category.description: Repositories that contain compiled font binaries (.ttf, .otf) but no source files or build system. These may be distribution-only repos or repos where the source is maintained elsewhere.

by_category.label: Unknown / empty
by_category.description: Repositories that don't match any known pattern. These may be empty, contain only documentation, or use an unrecognized project structure.
